  "texts": [
    "Confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and services are paramount concerns in the IoT landscape [31].",
    "Safeguarding confidentiality, ensuring the integrity of transmitted and stored information, and guaranteeing the availability of critical services require robust security measures, including encryption, access control mechanisms, intrusion detection systems, and redundancy planning.",
    "In addition to security, privacy is a fundamental right that must be preserved in the IoT ecosystem [32].",
    "Collecting and processing vast amounts of personal data through IoT devices can lead to privacy breaches and expose individuals to various risks.",
    "Implementing privacy-by-design principles, ensuring user consent, and adopting privacy-enhancing technologies are crucial to protecting individuals' privacy within the IoT framework [33]."
